Subject: Re: [T2] how do I get mold off the inside of the pop-top roof?

On 3/13/05 11:44 AM, "E. Marc Coe" <marccoe(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> Anyway, I'm moving on to the interior.  There are spots of mold, quite a few,
> on the inside of the pop-top.  I would like to remove them, and I'm nervous
> about bleach, because I don't want to have a bunch of white spots on the roof.

I used a very weak soution of bleach. It's mold so bleach is perfect for
removing it.

If you rub too hard the fibres will wash off and leave patches so I
recommend that you go slowly and gently. Use a wet rag to clean, not a brush
and pat it dry with a towel.

